Lisette Verheig was already here.
As well as the teacher of traditional Chinese medicine, Cynthia Bogard, who called Bukenberg "the soul of Speykenisse that had long been lacking."
Reason: A few weeks before the opening, each resident received an invitation to donate a book from his own congregation.
