The idea worked.
The shelves are fixed upstairs.
"There's nothing worse than a half-empty library," says architect Vini Maas.
"I think, thanks to our invitation, every resident now has some connection to this new house.
Everyone knows that his book is part of this building.
Even if it only serves to decorate.
Thus, the MVRDV was able to solve a royal problem called the creation of identity on a professional jargon.
Speykenisse wrote his literary story.
