Hector Hetin Reyes, a long-standing basketball traveler, has been involved in this sport for over 60 years and, thanks to him, has traveled around the world.
Few people in Puerto Rico remember as many basketball stories as Hector Hetin Reyes.
And before the brain hemorrhaging tied him to a wheelchair in 2008, Reyes was put into sports for more than 60 years, as a small player, a basketball player, a commissioner and head of BSN with the Baymon Cowboys and the president of the Basketball Federation.
